<h3>Stress Management</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Relax your mind</li>
  <ul>
    <li>Write</li>
    <li>Let your feelings out</li>
    <li>Do something you enjoy</li>
    <li>Focus on the present</li>
  </ul>
  <li>Relax your body</li>
  <ul>
    <li>Exercise regularly</li>
    <li>Sufficient sleep</li>
    <li>Breathing exercises</li>
    <li>Progressive muscle relaxation</li>
  </ul>
  <li>Reduce stress</li>
  <ul>
    <li>Manage your time</li>
    <li>Find balance and purpose in your life</li>
    <li>Get support</li>
    <li>Change your thinking</li>
  </ul>
  <li>Additional information and resources</li>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.helpguide.org/articles/stress/stress-management.htm" target="_blank">Detailed information</a></li>
    <li><a href="http://www.nacada.ksu.edu/Resources/Clearinghouse/View-Articles/Stress-Management-Resource-Links.aspx" target="_blank">Resources</a></li>
  </ul>
</ul>
<h3>Test Taking</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Overview</li>
  <ul>
    <li>Understand the Directions</li>
    <li>Budget time</li>
    <li>Skip and go back to questions you don't know</li>
    <li>Check answers</li>
  </ul>
  <li>Multiple Choice Questions</li>
  <ul>
    <li>Read all the answers</li>
    <li>Eliminate wrong answers</li>
  </ul>
  <li>Reading Passages</li>
  <ul>
    <li>Hone in on relevant points</li>
    <li>Mark key words and ideas</li>
    <li>Utilize text features</li>
  </ul>
  <li>Essay Questions</li>
  <ul>
    <li>Create an outline</li>
    <li>Make sure you answer the question</li>
  </ul>
  <li>Math Questions</li>
  <ul>
    <li>Show work</li>
    <li>Write legibly</li>
    <li>Check for careless errors</li>
  </ul>
  <li>Additional Information</li>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://casc.byu.edu/testtaking-strategies" target="_blank">More test strategies</a></li>
    <li><a href="http://www.nacada.ksu.edu/Resources/Clearinghouse/View-Articles/Test-taking-Resource-Links.aspx" target="_blank">Test taking resources</a></li>
  </ul>
</ul>
<h3>Studying</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Give yourself enough time to study</li>
  <li>Create an organized study space</li>
  <li>Use visual aids</li>
  <li>Practice old tests and homework</li>
  <li>Explain concepts to others</li>
  <li>Have a productive study group</li>
  <li>Take breaks</li>
  <li>Eat and drink well</li>
  <li>Plan for test</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/studying/effective-studying/top-40-study-strategies" target="_blank">Additional strategies</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.educationcorner.com/study-skills.html" target="_blank">Study skills resources</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.google.com/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=18&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=0ahUKEwjpg_z_9NPYAhVX0WMKHWZ_Dz4QtwIIhgEwEQ&url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dp60rN9JEapg&usg=AOvVaw0bLSOm8y7KFNH2sxn9eL5M" target="_blank">Study tips video</a></li>
</ul>
<h3>Time Management</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Know your goals</li>
  <li>Prioritize wisely</li>
  <li>Plan ahead</li>
  <li>Eliminate distractions</li>
  <li>Take care of yourself</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.mindtools.com/pages/article/newHTE_00.htm" target="_blank">Additional information</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://www.nacada.ksu.edu/Resources/Clearinghouse/View-Articles/Time-Management-Resource-Links.aspx" target="_blank">Time management resources</a></li>
</ul>
<h3>Decision Making</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Define the problem</li>
  <li>Establish the criteria</li>
  <li>Conside the alternatives</li>
  <li>Identify the best alternative</li>
  <li>Develop and Implement a plan of action</li>
  <li>Evaluate decision</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.umassd.edu/fycm/decisionmaking/process/" target="_blank">Another decision making model</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://www.dartmouth-hitchcock.org/medical-information/decision-making-resources.html" target="_blank">Decision making resources</a></li>
</ol>

